name: Center
opera: Ordered to go to the airport and meet the special investigation team

name: AIRPORT
opera: Ordered to go to the airport and meet the special investigation team

name: NPP
opera: The boss of the investigation team is a beautiful woman, awesome, and more motivated to fight zombies

name: SPM
opera: Lucky to pass the street, back to the hotel and hope for a good night's sleep

name: ST
opera: The radio is broken again, go to the police station and find a backup radio to contact the headquarters

name: Hostel
opera: Reconnected with the headquarters and received a mission to go to the factory (the other side didn't expect that we were still alive, and so was I)

name: PD
opera: Control the factory, but attract many zombies, destroy them on the trail

name: Factory
opera: It's getting colder and we need more warmth, maybe something good can be found in the hotel

name: Alley
opera: The hotel is really a treasure, harvesting a batch of supplies (only canned luncheon meat), ensuring the safe delivery of supplies to the park

name: Hotel
opera: The ammunition supply cannot be delivered because of the broken bridge. If you want to live, you can only go to the broken bridge to receive it. This is a suicide act, which is funny

name: Park
opera: Lost 2 companions, this disaster will take a long time, go to the convenience store to find supplies

name: Broken bridge
opera: Found a new path near the base, to avoid accidents, to investigate

name: CVS
opera: The original house is in ruins, the noisy neighbors who were annoying before, and now I still miss their nagging

name: Path
opera: There are zombies on the way back, I accidentally got separated, unlucky

name: Ruins
opera: I remember last time I got slapped by my ex-girlfriend here

name: Center
opera: This time, we will go on a mission with the beautiful commissioner! Will there be peach blossom luck?

name: AIRPORT
opera: Zombies mutate faster, split into different types, and become more and more difficult

name: NPP
opera: The chances of encountering living people in the city are getting lower and lower. I don’t know how my mother is. I miss the sandwiches she made.
